cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with data analysis queries on two-dimensional points, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The use of geometric queries such as dominance and rectangle visibility suggests that it may also belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The inclusion of semigroup and group queries such as sum, average, variance, minimum and maximum suggests that it may also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. Finally, the consideration of top-$k$ queries and mode suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
